<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="532" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1255,1640]" pageId="1" pageNumber="532">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1255,1280]" pageId="1" pageNumber="532">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Body narrow and elongated, no conglobation ability. Head and anterior pereon tergites bearing tubercles not protruding backwards from posterior margins.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="532" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1255,1640]" pageId="1" pageNumber="532">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1327,1352]" pageId="1" pageNumber="532">Remarks</emphasis>
. The two subgenera differ from each other not only in terms of morphological characters, but also in terms of behavioral and reproductive strategies. The members of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Verhoeff" authorityYear="1930" box="[898,1023,1364,1389]" class="Malacostraca" family="Agnaridae" genus="Hemilepistus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="545" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Desertellio">
<emphasis box="[898,1023,1364,1389]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="532">Desertellio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are iteroparous species living under stones and in the leaf litters and the soil crevices (
<bibRefCitation author="Roder, G. &amp; Linsenmayr, K." box="[711,1018,1399,1424]" pageId="1" pageNumber="532" pagination="349 - 369" refId="ref6043" refString="Roder, G. &amp; Linsenmayr, K. (1999) The mating system on the subsocial desert woodlouse Hemilepistus elongatus (Isopoda, Oniscidea): a model of an evolutionary step towards monogamy in the genus Hemilepistus sensu stricto? Ethology, Ecology &amp; Evolution, 11, 349 - 369. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 08927014.1999.9522819" type="journal article" year="1999">RÃ¶der &amp; Linsenmayr 1999</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Kashani, G. M. &amp; Sari, A." box="[1030,1271,1399,1424]" pageId="1" pageNumber="532" pagination="13 - 22" refId="ref5648" refString="Kashani, G. M. &amp; Sari, A. (2012) Discovery of Hemilepistus elongatus Budde-Lund, 1885 (Isopoda, Oniscidea) in Iran: redescription and intraspecific character variability. ZooKeys, 176, 13 - 22. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 176.2271" type="journal article" year="2012">Kashani &amp; Sari 2012</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Budde-Lund" authorityYear="1910" box="[1290,1436,1399,1424]" class="Malacostraca" family="Agnaridae" genus="Hemilepistus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="532" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1290,1436,1399,1424]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="532">Hemilepistus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species, however, indicate behavioral adaptations for living in arid habitats, where these semelparous species dig burrow into the soil in which they make monogamous pairs and take care of the offspring until the next breeding season (
<bibRefCitation author="Linsenmair, K." box="[240,435,1508,1533]" pageId="1" pageNumber="532" pagination="131 - 162" refId="ref5920" refString="Linsenmair, K. (1972) Die Bedeutung familienspezifischer &quot; Abzeichen &quot; fur den Familienzusammenhalt bei der sozialen Wustenassel Hemilepistus reaumuri Audouin u. Savigny (Crustacea, Isopoda, Oniscoidea). Zeitschrift fur Tierpsychologie, 31, 131 - 162." type="journal article" year="1972">Linsenmair 1972</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Linsenmair, K." box="[446,505,1508,1532]" pageId="1" pageNumber="532" pagination="423 - 453" refId="ref5964" refString="Linsenmair, K. (1984) Comparative studies in the social behaviour of the desert isopod Hemilepistus reaumuri and of a Porcellio species. Symposia of the Zoological Society of London, 53, 423 - 453." type="journal article" year="1984">1984</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Shachak, M. &amp; Steinberger, Y. &amp; Or, Y." box="[517,741,1508,1533]" pageId="1" pageNumber="532" pagination="133 - 140" refId="ref6240" refString="Shachak, M., Steinberger, Y. &amp; Or, Y. (1979) Phenology, activity and regulation of radiation load in the desert isopod, Hemilepistus reaumuri. Oecologia, 40, 133 - 140. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / BF 00347931" type="journal article" year="1979">
Shachak 
<emphasis box="[619,668,1508,1533]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="532">et al</emphasis>
. 1979
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Shachak, M." box="[753,913,1508,1533]" pageId="1" pageNumber="532" pagination="404 - 413" refId="ref6200" refString="Shachak, M. (1980) Energy allocation and life history strategy of the desert isopod H. reaumuri. Oecologia, 45, 404 - 413. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / BF 00540214" type="journal article" year="1980">Shachak 1980</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Warburg, M. R." box="[925,1087,1508,1533]" pageId="1" pageNumber="532" pagination="45 - 62" refId="ref6359" refString="Warburg, M. R. (1994) Review of recent studies on reproduction in terrestrial isopods. Invertebrate Reproduction and Development, 26, 45 - 62. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 07924259.1994.9672400" type="journal article" year="1994">Warburg 1994</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kashani, G. M. &amp; Sari, A. &amp; Hosseinie, S." box="[1098,1321,1508,1533]" pageId="1" pageNumber="532" pagination="54 - 68" refId="ref5703" refString="Kashani, G. M., Sari, A. &amp; Hosseinie, S. (2010) Terrestrial isopods of the subgenus Hemilepistus (Hemilepistus) Budde-Lund, 1879 (Isopoda: Oniscidea) from Iran. Zootaxa, 2549, 54 - 68. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2549.1.3" type="journal article" year="2010">
Kashani 
<emphasis box="[1197,1245,1508,1533]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="532">et al</emphasis>
. 2010
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1255,1640]" pageId="1" pageNumber="532">
These remarkable differences between the two subgenera suggest the paraphyletic status of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Budde-Lund" authorityYear="1910" box="[151,297,1580,1605]" class="Malacostraca" family="Agnaridae" genus="Hemilepistus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="532" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,297,1580,1605]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="532">Hemilepistus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Spyros Sfenthourakis and Helmut Schmalfuss, personal communication) necessitating further investigations to clarify the ambiguities.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
